<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The for loop is for (i = 1; i < argc; ++i) where i is the loop counter. Later in the loop body the code does ++i when param_res == PERF_RPL_PARAM_STR_PLUS_NEXT. The assignment param_res = process_short_params_str(p + 1, p_next); determines that condition, so the function call in the body indirectly causes the loop counter to be modified inside the loop body. This violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.2 (clause 4): the loop counter shall not be modified in the for loop body.
</scenario>

